01/11/2005
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- The seventh edition of the Southeast Europe Economic Forum started in Sofia on Tuesday (1 November).
This year, the two-day event focuses on education, training and support aimed at boosting competitiveness in the small- and medium-sized enterprises sector.
Government officials, industry leaders, members of the business community, entrepreneurs, investors, financial institutions and international organisations engaged in the region are attending the forum.
(bTV - 01/11/05)
